<br>
1) Set up a dot fund.  All vendor loot from raids goes into it, the controlling person passes out the dots.  Perhaps encourage the members to donate a set up fee.<br>
<br>
2)  Give the vendor loot to the clerics casting Symbol/Aego.<br>
<br>
3)  Have each member of the raid bring xx amount of dots, and give the cleric the dots as used or at the beginning of the raid.  This amount varies depending on deaths, length of the raid, whether it's Symbol or Aego (Aego lasts 2.5 hours, Symbol 20 mins).<br>
<br>
DBN uses option 1, and I usually carry 2 10-slots of dots around with me to pass out to our clerics, as well as our Giant's Bane Wizzies and Runing Chanters...please don't forget the chanters if they are runing the main tank, or themselves (helps keep them alive to do those mez's). <p><center><font face="Monotype Corsiva" size="5" color="#C0C0C0"><strong>Edwina Nytengayle<br> </strong></font></center>

